#CQ: How many battery passports are attributed to a single battery item?
#Story: As a regulatory authority, I want to verify how many battery passports are attributed to a single battery item, so that I can ensure each battery item has a unique and unambiguous digital record, preventing duplication or fraud in the battery passport system.
#CQ: Does the battery identifier of a battery item relate to the battery item level of granularity?
#Story: As a regulatory authority, I want to verify that the battery identifier of a battery item relates to the battery item level of granularity, so that I can confirm that identification is applied at the correct level of specificity, ensuring traceability down to each individual battery item as required by regulation.
#CQ: Which battery categories require the date of putting the battery into service to be recorded in the battery passport?
#Story: As a regulatory authority, I want to identify which battery categories require the date of putting the battery into service to be recorded in the battery passport, so that I can enforce compliance and ensure economic operators fulfil their data recording obligations.
#CQ: When must a new battery passport be issued for a battery item that has been subject to remanufacturing, repurposing, or treatment operations preparing for re-use or repurposing?
#Story: As an economic operator, I want to determine when a new battery passport must be issued for a battery item subject to remanufacturing, repurposing, or treatment operations preparing for re-use or repurposing, so that I can fulfil my regulatory obligations and ensure the battery status is accurately updated.
#CQ: What is the current self-discharge rate of a battery item at a given aging parameter?
#Story: As a recycler, I want to access the current self-discharge rate of a battery item at a given aging parameter, so that I can evaluate the actual condition of the battery item and make informed decisions about its suitability for re-use, repurposing, or end-of-life processing.
#CQ: Is the number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item a static or dynamic data attribute in the battery passport?
#Story: As a recycler, I want to determine whether the number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item is a static or dynamic data attribute in the battery passport, so that I can assess whether the recorded cycle data reflects the battery item's current state for repurposing or remanufacturing decisions.
#CQ: Does the non-cycle application exception apply to the number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item recorded in the battery passport?
#Story: As an auditor, I want to verify whether the non-cycle application exception applies to the number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item recorded in the battery passport, so that I can confirm the manufacturer's reporting obligations are correctly fulfilled under Regulation (EU) 2023/1542.
#CQ: Does the battery passport include periodically recorded information on the operating environmental temperature conditions for a battery item?
#Story: As a recycler, I want to verify whether the battery passport includes periodically recorded information on the operating environmental temperature conditions for a battery item, so that I can assess temperature-related degradation and determine the battery item's suitability for preparation for re-use or repurposing.
#CQ: What unit is used to express temperature information in a battery passport?
#Story: As a sustainability analyst, I want to verify the unit used to express operating environmental temperature conditions recorded in a battery passport for a battery item, so that I can ensure data consistency and comparability across different battery passports during environmental performance assessments.
#CQ: Does the battery passport use histograms to represent the time spent charging in extreme temperatures for a battery item?
#Story: As a recycler, I want to confirm whether the battery passport uses histograms to represent the time spent charging in extreme temperatures for a battery item, so that I can accurately interpret thermal stress history and assess the remaining safe usability of the battery before processing.
#
@prefix : <http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@base <http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton/> .

<http://www.semanticweb.org/DPP_Skeleton> rdf:type owl:Ontology .


:hasBatteryPassport rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :BatteryItem ;
    rdfs:range :DPP ;
    rdfs:label "hasBatteryPassport" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a BatteryItem to the DPP(s) attributed to it. Used to answer: 'How many battery passports are attributed to a single battery item?' by counting the DPPs linked via this property." .

:aboutBatteryItem rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :BatteryItem ;
    rdfs:label "aboutBatteryItem" ;
    rdfs:comment "Associates any DataElement in a DPP with the BatteryItem it describes. Used to verify that a battery identifier relates to the battery item level of granularity, and to scope measurements (e.g., temperature, cycles, self-discharge) to the correct item." .

:requiresDataElement rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :BatteryCategory ;
    rdfs:range :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "requiresDataElement" ;
    rdfs:comment "Declares that a BatteryCategory requires a specific DataElement to be recorded in the battery passport. Used to answer: 'Which battery categories require the date of putting the battery into service to be recorded in the battery passport?' by selecting BatteryCategory that require ServiceStartDate." .

:triggeredByOperation rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :NewPassportIssuance ;
    rdfs:range :ProcessingOperation ;
    rdfs:label "triggeredByOperation" ;
    rdfs:comment "Indicates which ProcessingOperation(s) trigger the issuance of a new battery passport for an item. Used to answer: 'When must a new battery passport be issued for a battery item that has been subject to remanufacturing, repurposing, or treatment preparing for re-use or repurposing?'" .

:hasApplicableException rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :Exception ;
    rdfs:label "hasApplicableException" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a DataElement to an Exception that applies to it. Used to answer: 'Does the non-cycle application exception apply to the number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item recorded in the battery passport?'" .

:usesRepresentation rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :RepresentationType ;
    rdfs:label "usesRepresentation" ;
    rdfs:comment "Specifies how a DataElement is represented (e.g., histogram). Used to answer: 'Does the battery passport use histograms to represent the time spent charging in extreme temperatures for a battery item?'" .

:hasMeasurementTime rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :MeasurementTime ;
    rdfs:label "hasMeasurementTime" ;
    rdfs:comment "Attaches a reified timestamp (MeasurementTime) to a DataElement. Used to qualify time-varying measurements (e.g., self-discharge rate, operating temperature) with xsd:dateTimeStamp as required." .

:hasAgingParameter rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :AgingParameter ;
    rdfs:label "hasAgingParameter" ;
    rdfs:comment "Attaches a reified AgingParameter to a measurement DataElement (e.g., self-discharge rate) to answer: 'What is the current self-discharge rate of a battery item at a given aging parameter?'" .

:hasTemperatureValue rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :TemperatureValue ;
    rdfs:label "hasTemperatureValue" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a temperature-related DataElement to its temperature value element, enabling unit and value capture for operating environmental temperature conditions." .

:hasSelfDischargeRateValue rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :has_Value_Element ;
    rdfs:domain :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:range :SelfDischargeRateValue ;
    rdfs:label "hasSelfDischargeRateValue" ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a SelfDischargeRate DataElement to its value element, enabling unit and value capture for the rate." .

:DataElement_Unit rdf:type owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:subPropertyOf :ValueElement ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Unit" ;
    rdfs:comment "Unit of measurement for a ValueElement (e.g., '°C' for temperature, '%/month' for self-discharge). Used to answer: 'What unit is used to express temperature information in a battery passport?'" .

:BatteryItem rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Battery Item" ;
    rdfs:comment "An individual battery for which a passport may be issued and item-level data are recorded. Used as the anchor for counting passports and scoping item-level identifiers and measurements." .

:BatteryCategory rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Battery Category" ;
    rdfs:comment "Regulatory category of batteries (e.g., portable, LMT, EV, industrial). Linked via requiresDataElement to mandated data (e.g., ServiceStartDate)." .

:ProcessingOperation rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Processing Operation" ;
    rdfs:comment "An operation that may change a battery's status (e.g., remanufacturing, repurposing, preparation for re-use). Used to trigger new passport issuance requirements." .

:Remanufacturing rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ProcessingOperation ;
    rdfs:label "Remanufacturing" ;
    rdfs:comment "ProcessingOperation subclass representing remanufacturing." .

:Repurposing rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ProcessingOperation ;
    rdfs:label "Repurposing" ;
    rdfs:comment "ProcessingOperation subclass representing repurposing." .

:PreparationForReUseOrRepurposing rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ProcessingOperation ;
    rdfs:label "Preparation for Re-use or Repurposing" ;
    rdfs:comment "ProcessingOperation subclass representing treatment operations preparing for re-use or repurposing." .

:BatteryIdentifier rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Battery Identifier" ;
    rdfs:comment "Item-level identifier recorded in the DPP. Linked via aboutBatteryItem to the BatteryItem it identifies to verify correct level of granularity." .

:ServiceStartDate rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Service Start Date" ;
    rdfs:comment "Date/time when the battery is put into service. Categories that require this in the DPP are linked via requiresDataElement." .

:NewPassportIssuance rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "New Passport Issuance" ;
    rdfs:comment "A requirement data element indicating when a new DPP must be issued; qualified by triggeredByOperation for operations like remanufacturing, repurposing, and preparation for re-use/repurposing." .

:SelfDischargeRate rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :MultiValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Self-Discharge Rate" ;
    rdfs:comment "A measurement data element for the battery item's self-discharge rate. Uses value elements for the rate (hasSelfDischargeRateValue), the measurement time (hasMeasurementTime), and the aging parameter (hasAgingParameter)." .

:FullCycleCount rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :SingleValueDataElement , :DynamicDataAttribute ;
    rdfs:label "Full Cycle Count" ;
    rdfs:comment "Number of full charging and discharging cycles of a battery item, recorded in the DPP. Classified as a DynamicDataAttribute to answer whether it is static or dynamic; exceptions can be linked via hasApplicableException." .

:PeriodicDataElement rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :MultiValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Periodic Data Element" ;
    rdfs:comment "A multi-valued data element intended for periodically recorded observations, each qualified by time via hasMeasurementTime." .

:OperatingTemperature rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :PeriodicDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Operating Environmental Temperature" ;
    rdfs:comment "Periodically recorded operating environmental temperature conditions for a battery item. Uses hasTemperatureValue (with DataElement_Unit) and hasMeasurementTime. Presence in a DPP answers whether such periodic information is included." .

:ExtremeTemperatureChargingTime rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :MultiValueDataElement ;
    rdfs:label "Extreme Temperature Charging Time" ;
    rdfs:comment "Data element representing time spent charging in extreme temperatures for a battery item. Its representation type (e.g., histogram) is indicated via usesRepresentation." .

:StaticDataAttribute rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Static Data Attribute" ;
    rdfs:comment "Marker class for data elements whose values do not change over time in the DPP. Used to classify attributes for CQ on static vs dynamic." .

:DynamicDataAttribute rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :DataElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Dynamic Data Attribute" ;
    rdfs:comment "Marker class for data elements whose values may change over time in the DPP. Used to classify attributes for CQ on static vs dynamic." .

:Exception rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Exception" ;
    rdfs:comment "A regulatory exception that may apply to a data element recorded in the DPP." .

:NonCycleApplicationException rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :Exception ;
    rdfs:label "Non-Cycle Application Exception" ;
    rdfs:comment "Specific exception indicating non-cycle application conditions. Used with hasApplicableException to check if it applies to FullCycleCount." .

:RepresentationType rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Representation Type" ;
    rdfs:comment "Abstract representation style for a data element (e.g., histogram)." .

:HistogramRepresentation rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :RepresentationType ;
    rdfs:label "Histogram Representation" ;
    rdfs:comment "RepresentationType indicating that the data element is expressed as a histogram." .

:SelfDischargeRateValue rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Self-Discharge Rate Value" ;
    rdfs:comment "Value element carrying the numeric self-discharge rate and its unit (via DataElement_Unit)." .

:AgingParameter rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Aging Parameter" ;
    rdfs:comment "Reified qualifier for measurements capturing the aging parameter (e.g., SOH, calendar age). Used with hasAgingParameter." .

:MeasurementTime rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Measurement Time" ;
    rdfs:comment "Reified time qualifier for measurements; its timestamp is given via DataElement_Value with xsd:dateTimeStamp. Used with hasMeasurementTime." .

:TemperatureValue rdf:type owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :ValueElementReification ;
    rdfs:label "Temperature Value" ;
    rdfs:comment "Value element carrying a temperature measurement and its unit (via DataElement_Unit) for operating environmental temperature conditions." .


:has_Name rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty;
rdfs:label "has_Name" .

:hasCity rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty;
rdfs:label "hasCity" .
